# Copy to `.env` (same directory) and fill in. `.env` is gitignored and must STAY
# gitignored: this repo is handed to judges, and a key committed once lives in the
# git history forever, even after the file is deleted. GitHub's secret scanning will
# also flag it and Google may auto-revoke the key -- possibly mid-demo.
#
#   cp .env.example .env      # then paste your key below
#
# Optional in every sense: with no key the analyzer falls back to rules, loudly and
# instantly. Rules is the deterministic, rehearsed path and the one to demo on.

GEMINI_API_KEY=

# Optional. Leave unset to use the default alias `gemini-flash-latest`, which is the
# most robust choice: a PINNED id can 404 with "no longer available to new users" on a
# newer project (the models endpoint still lists it -- listing is not callability), and
# free-tier quota is per-project-PER-MODEL so a 429 on one model says nothing about
# another. If you do pin one and it fails, the analyzer says which model and which
# status code, then falls back to rules.
# GEMINI_MODEL=gemini-flash-latest
